cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the issue of de-anonymizing programmers from executable binaries, which is a security and privacy concern. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves machine learning techniques and source code authorship attribution, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the use of stylistic representations embedded in assembly and the evaluation on data from the Google Code Jam indicate that it could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
